# Server Actions

## Structure

- Always start with `'use server'`
- Always authenticate with `requireUser()` from `@/lib/auth`
- Get tenantId via `user.memberships[0].tenantId`
- Validate input with Zod
- Wrap DB mutations in try/catch
- Call `revalidatePath()` after mutations
- Use `redirect()` for navigation after create/delete
- Return `{ error: string }` or `{ success: true }` — never throw from actions

```typescript
'use server';
import { requireUser } from '@/lib/auth';
import { prisma } from '@/lib/prisma';
import { revalidatePath } from 'next/cache';

export async function updateAction(prev: State, fd: FormData): Promise<State> {
  const user = await requireUser();
  const tenantId = user.memberships[0].tenantId;
  // validate, mutate, revalidate
}
```

## Email Triggers

After successful mutations, fire relevant emails from `lib/email.ts`. Always fire-and-forget:

```typescript
import { sendNewLeadEmail } from '@/lib/email';

// After creating the lead:
sendNewLeadEmail(owner.email, owner.name, leadData).catch(console.error);
```

| Action | Email Function |
|--------|---------------|
| User registration | `sendWelcomeEmail` |
| Password reset request | `sendPasswordResetEmail` |
| Lead submitted | `sendNewLeadEmail` + `sendLeadConfirmationEmail` |
| Domain verified | `sendDomainVerifiedEmail` |
| Team member added | `sendTeamInviteEmail` |
| Site published | `sendSitePublishedEmail` |

## Auth Actions (no `requireUser`)

Auth actions in `app/(auth)/` don't call `requireUser()` — they handle unauthenticated users:
- `loginAction` — validates credentials, creates session, redirects to `/dashboard`
- `registerAction` — creates user + tenant + content, sends welcome email, redirects to `/onboarding`
- `forgotPasswordAction` — generates reset token, sends email (always returns success to prevent enumeration)
- `resetPasswordAction` — validates token, updates password, invalidates all sessions, redirects to `/login?reset=success`
